                                  <p class="mb-4 size-18">At Marshall University in Huntington, West Virginia, College of Liberal Arts students can earn a Bachelor of Arts (BA) degree in Economics in order to analyze important economic problems and issues affecting society. The areas that Marshall Economics majors learn about include: unemployment, inflation, economic growth and development, government taxation and spending policies, environmental degradation and protection, the distribution of income and wealth, international trading and financial arrangements.</p>
                                    <p class="mb-4 size-18">Economics majors in the College of Liberal Arts deepen their understanding of the U.S. economy and other global economies. With a bachelor’s degree in Economics, Marshall students are ready for a changing world because they’re equipped with problem-solving and analytical skills relevant to a wide range of career paths: law, finance, foreign affairs, policy analysis, health administration, journalism and more.</p>
