                                                      <h3 class="highlight header-colorize text-uppercase mb-4"><a href="https://www.marshall.edu/academics/programs/psychology-ba/">Psychology, B.A.</a></h3>
                                                          <p class="mb-4 size-18">The study of psychology equips students with the latest skills and tools to explore human behavior and better understand how we think, act and feel. Careers for psychology majors are wide-ranging. A psychology bachelor’s degree prepares graduates to practice in this specialized field or to pursue a wide range of professions throughout business, law, medicine and more.</p>
                                                            <p class="mb-4 size-18">As an undergraduate in the Bachelor of Arts (B.A.) in Psychology degree program at Marshall University in Huntington, West Virginia, you’ll learn with excellent faculty who help you develop a culturally sensitive lens through which to better understand human nature. You’ll also learn about research design, data management, program development, training, observation, critical thinking, abstract idea synthesis and technical writing. The many skills you’ll learn as a Psychology major will benefit you in a wide range of workplaces, and in graduate and professional school settings.</p>
                                                      <h4 class="header-colorize">Why Study Psychology at Marshall?</h4>
                                                      <p class="mb-4 size-18">As an undergraduate at Marshall University in Huntington, West Virginia, you can earn your B.A. in Psychology in three to four years, attending full time.</p>
                                                      <p class="mb-4 size-18">Marshall’s Psychology program reflects a wide range of faculty interests, enabling our students to explore many areas of this discipline. Faculty members are also involved in various department, campus and community organizations, interacting with and getting to know Marshall students.</p>
                                                      <p class="mb-4 size-18">Faculty are very focused on the needs of individual students and will often make room in their schedules to provide specialized experiences such as internships and research projects that further prepare Psychology majors. At Marshall, you can count on your professors for intensive advising to help you select and maintain a productive and fulfilling career path.</p>
                                                      <p class="mb-4 size-18">The Psychology program strives to create a supportive, family-like atmosphere in our undergraduate and graduate programs to encourage collaboration and support rather than competition. As a result, Marshall’s attrition rate is low and our licensure and employment rate is strong in West Virginia and beyond.</p>
                                                      <p class="mb-4 size-18">Marshall offers students robust graduate programs in Psychology. Marshall’s Doctor of Psychology (Psy.D.) program is accredited by the American Psychological Association; it provides more than half of the doctoral-level psychologists licensed in the state of West Virginia each year. The program has also been awarded a Health Resources and Services Administration (HRSA) Graduate Psychology Education Grant for the past five years. Master’s degree programs in Psychology at Marshall have also received the HRSA Behavioral Health Workforce Education and Training Grant. Undergraduate students who meet the necessary requirements can apply to Marshall’s accelerated master’s degree program in Psychology to begin taking up to 12 hours in graduate coursework in place of elective undergraduate courses.</p>
